name: Franklin Brandywine Global Income Optimiser Fund
longDescription: To achieve its investment objective invests primarily in debt instruments of issuers anywhere in the world while following a sustainable investment approach. May invest in debt instruments including fixed-income and floating-rate instruments, government and corporate bonds, and inflation-linked bonds, may invest in corporate loans, including syndicated loans; seeks to hedge, as completely as possible, against changes in its NAV that would otherwise result from the changes in the U.S. dollar or Canadian dollar exchange rate. Franklin Brandywine Global Sustainable Income Optimiser Active ETF seeks to provide high current income and  preservation of capital through exposure to global debt instruments.
